\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces A whimsical, full-page scene depicting a person sitting on the edge of a bathtub, staring at a bathroom floor tiled with white unit squares. On the floor, three regions of tiles are outlined in colored chalk: a $3 \times 3$ blue square, a $4 \times 4$ gold square, and a $5 \times 5$ coral square, arranged to form the classic Pythagorean theorem diagram around a right triangle drawn in the grout lines. A thought bubble above the person's head contains a branching tree with the labels $(3,4,5)$ at the root, branching into three children, each branching into three more --- fading into a fractal haze. The bathtub is overflowing slightly, unnoticed. On the windowsill behind, a small clay tablet (Plimpton 322) leans against a rubber duck.}}{lxi}{figure.caption.4}\protected@file@percent }
