\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.12}{\ignorespaces A bar chart with three groups of bars, one for each branch (Left, Middle, Right), showing the hypotenuses at levels 0 through 4. The Middle branch bars rocket upward exponentially (5, 29, 169, 985, 5741), dwarfing the other two branches. The Left branch grows modestly (5, 13, 25, 41, 61...) and the Right branch similarly (5, 17, 37, 65...). The visual contrast --- one skyscraper among bungalows --- makes the exponential-vs.-moderate growth vivid.}}{65}{figure.caption.39}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.13}{\ignorespaces A number line running horizontally across the page, with the middle-branch hypotenuses $5, 29, 169, 985, 5741$ marked at their positions (not to scale --- logarithmic spacing). Curved arrows arc above the number line, connecting successive pairs, each annotated with "$\times 6$" and "$-1\times $" (i.e., "$6c_n - c_{n-1}$"). The arrow from $29$ to $169$ is highlighted, with the computation $6 \times 29 - 5 = 169$ written below. The value $169 = 13^2$ is boxed and starred.}}{67}{figure.caption.40}\protected@file@percent }
