\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.14}{\ignorespaces Three subtrees of the Berggren tree drawn side by side, one for each branch (Left in red, Middle in blue, Right in green). All three are rooted at the same parent node $(3, 4, 5)$, shown in grey at the top. The subtrees' nodes are colored accordingly, and a prominent "no duplicates" symbol --- a circle with a diagonal line through two overlapping shapes --- hovers at the center where the three subtrees would intersect if they could. The visual message: the three families never intermarry.}}{69}{figure.caption.41}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.15}{\ignorespaces A flowchart-style diagram, elegant and vertical. \textbf  {Input box} at the top: "A composite number $N$." \textbf  {Arrow down} to \textbf  {Step 1}: "Find a Pythagorean triple $(a, b, c)$ with $a = N$." The Berggren tree is sketched faintly in the background, suggesting the source of triples. \textbf  {Arrow down} to \textbf  {Step 2}: "Compute $c - b$ and $c + b$." Two numbers appear on cards. \textbf  {Arrow down} to \textbf  {Step 3}: "Compute $\gcd (c - b, N)$." A gear icon. \textbf  {Arrow down} to a \textbf  {diamond decision box}: "Is $1 < \gcd < N$?" \textbf  {Yes arrow} leads to \textbf  {Output}: "Nontrivial factor found! (party)" \textbf  {No arrow} loops back with the label "Try another triple."}}{71}{figure.caption.42}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.16}{\ignorespaces The specific worked example for $(21, 20, 29)$, laid out as a visual "proof without words." At the top, the right triangle with sides $21$, $20$, $29$. Below it, a horizontal arrow from $29$ to $20$ labeled "$29 - 20 = 9$." Below that, a Venn-diagram-style overlap of the divisors of $9$ ($\{1, 3, 9\}$) and the divisors of $21$ ($\{1, 3, 7, 21\}$), with $\{1, 3\}$ in the overlap. The GCD $3$ is circled in red. At the bottom, the conclusion: $21 = 3 \times 7$, written in large, satisfying numerals.}}{72}{figure.caption.43}\protected@file@percent }
