\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8.13}{\ignorespaces A graph of $\log (\text  {factoring time})$ vs. $\log N$. Three curves: (1) Trial division / Tree: a straight line with slope $1/2$ (labeled $\sqrt  {N}$); (2) Quadratic sieve / NFS: a curve that bends dramatically downward (labeled "sub-exponential"); (3) A hypothetical horizontal line labeled "polynomial?" with a question mark. The region between the curves is shaded, with the caption: "Where do quantum computers land?"}}{204}{figure.caption.116}\protected@file@percent }
