\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {13.11}{\ignorespaces A number line from $1.0$ to $1.5$ showing the ratios $d/a$ for successive Pell solutions: $3/2 = 1.500$, $17/12 = 1.417$, $99/70 = 1.414\overline  {285}$, $577/408 = 1.41421\overline  {568}$. A dashed horizontal asymptote at $\sqrt  {2} \approx 1.41421356\ldots  $ sits just below the descending sequence. Below each ratio, show the corresponding quadruple $(a, a, 1, d)$: $(2, 2, 1, 3)$, $(12, 12, 1, 17)$, $(70, 70, 1, 99)$, $(408, 408, 1, 577)$. Caption: "Pell's staircase --- quadruples that almost balance, forever approaching $\sqrt  {2}$."}}{333}{figure.caption.191}\protected@file@percent }
