\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {16.1}{\ignorespaces A whimsical "magic box" diagram. Three labeled machines --- $A$, $B$, $C$ --- each drawn as brass-and-gear contraptions in a Victorian style, reminiscent of Babbage's Difference Engine. A triple $(a, b, c)$ enters the top of each machine via a hopper; a new triple exits the bottom on a conveyor belt. A glowing analogue meter on the side of each machine is labeled "$Q$" and displays the same numerical value at input and output, emphasizing the invariance of the quadratic form. Steam curls decoratively from copper pipes.}}{384}{figure.caption.219}\protected@file@percent }
